At the moment, only Corporations are paying State income taxes, as no individual is subject to such taxes. I have noticed State-funded projects such as bicycle paths, road maintenance, unused docks, political pet projects like office buildings, state troopers, and more, which are not necessarily required within City limits. These and other expenditures significantly contribute to the State budget, and I have seen on TV how these funds are being used for city functions in larger cities. For instance, I watched a program where adg&g taught little ones how to ice fish, which I believe could have been done by the parents. Although I pay property taxes, I can assure you that when City residents receive the full bill without State funds, they will be more mindful of their spending, especially on office buildings. Instead of renting out large office spaces, I suggest renting only what is necessary, which could help the office rental market. In my previous business, I would often ask my managers, "how can we stop spending money?"
